         <abstract>
             <p>The monastic genealogy of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">St Takla Hāymānot</persName> that shows
             his spiritual descendance from <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1962Anthony">St Anthony</persName> and tells about his disciples
             and their spiritual successors. In part based on <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3973GadlaT">the Vita of Takla Hāymānot</ref>,
             a kind of monastic history of Ethiopia in the version of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0341DL">the monastery Dabra Libānos</placeName>.
             Mostly follows <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3973GadlaT">Gadla Takla Hāymānot (general record)</ref>.
            </p>
         </abstract>
